The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Thursday, September 2, 2004

 Road to avoid

 Rani Rashmoni Avenue at 1 pm. The CPI(M-L) trade union wing to rally. Traffic on SN Banerjee Road and Raja Subodh Mullick Square may be diverted.

 Cricket

 The Telegraph presents the 3rd Corporate amp; Club Indoor Cricket Tournament at Space Circle, 7 pm.

 Health

 Student Health Parliament an interaction on health issues to be organised by Bhagirathi Neotia Woman amp; Child Care Centre at Kala Kunj, 9.30 am.

 Discussion

 A talk on Whatever the festival, Calcutta cannot suffer from noise pollution, organised by Interact Club of Apeejay School, at BG-180, Salt Lake, 3 pm.

 Art watch

 Concepts amp; Ideas 2004, an exhibition of contemporary art work, on view at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.

 Aranya 2004, an exhibition on environment and forestry on view at Samokal Art Gallery, Gol Park, 2 pm to 8 pm.

 In camera

 Exposure: Portrait of a corporate crime an exhibition of photographs of the Bhopal disaster by Raghu Rai on view at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 11 am to 7 pm.

 Inheritance an exhibition of photographs on wildlife on display at Oxford Bookstore, Park Street.

 Meet

 Interactive programme for young citizens of India, organised by Actionaid, at Calcutta Samaritans, 48 Ripon Street, 10 am onwards. 

 Flamenco

 Flamenco workshop by dancer Rosanna Maya at Solace, 4, Sun-ny Park, from 11 am.




